    "This suggests that the opensource models assess essays more uniformly, clustering ratings around the midpoint, whereas human raters and the closed-source models provide a wider differentiation between essay qualities.",
    "Additionally, GPT-4, o1, and Mixtral provide significantly higher ratings than humans.",
    "The low rater correlation of both LLaMA 3 and Mixtral (Section 4.1) contributes to these observations by resulting in more average values and reduced variance.",
    "This highlights a limitation in the consistency and alignment of certain LLMs with human evaluative standards.",
